<h3 id="toc3"><span>Week of March 1st</span></h3>
<p>Would you mind housesitting? It's not an intensive job, I swear&#8230;</p>
<h4 id="toc4"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2508">SCP-2508</a> (&quot;<em>The Long Wait</em>&quot;) - Do you ever run your fingers along the walls of the dusty stairwell, sit on the front porch, and look up at the sky? You always will. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eekium" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2137346); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2137346&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="Eekium" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2137346)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eekium" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2137346); return false;">Eekium</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2375">SCP-2375</a> (&quot;The Recruiting Device&quot;) - GRU Division &quot;P&quot; are looking for new members. If you're interested, please turn on your TV and await further instructions. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-edmonds" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2562626); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2562626&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="Dr Edmonds" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2562626)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-edmonds" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2562626); return false;">Dr Edmonds</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2908">SCP-2908</a> (&quot;Golden cards of not death&quot;) - Pick a card, any card. It's the King, isn't it? You will come into great wealth - spoiler alert, it's because a truck full of pennies is going to fall on you. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomguy331" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2183741); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2183741&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="RandomGuy331" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2183741)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomguy331" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2183741); return false;">RandomGuy331</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-011-j">SCP-011-J</a> (&quot;The Baby&quot;) - Where's the anomaly&#8230; there he is! Where's the anomaly&#8230; there he is! <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/domeacolyte" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2230092); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2230092&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="DomeAcolyte" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2230092)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/domeacolyte" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2230092); return false;">DomeAcolyte</a></span> is currently busy playing peek-a-boo with the anomaly.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc5"><span>Tales</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/ofanendlesshunt-parttwo-rites-of-passage">Endless Hunt Part Two: Rites of Passage</a> (<a href="/ofanendlesshunt-partthree-riddlesfromthedark">Part Three: Riddles from the Dark</a>, <a href="/ofanendlesshunt-partfour-livingthroughshatteredglass">Part Four: Living Through Shattered Glass</a>, <a href="/ofanendlesshunt-partfive-theprisoner">Part Five: The Prisoner</a>) - The continuation of the series Of An Endless Hunt, Amy continues to go on the run, and explore the mystical and wondrous all the while. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rumetzen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(209204); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=209204&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="rumetzen" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=209204)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rumetzen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(209204); return false;">rumetzen</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc6"><span>Author Pages</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/j-cooper-s-personnel-file">The Personnel File of Joseph Cooper</a> - <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/choiwel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1628145); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1628145&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="Choiwel" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1628145)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/choiwel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1628145); return false;">Choiwel</a></span>'s author page! Joseph Cooper is an extremely lucky man, if you ask me. Barely surviving a brush with death, ending up through a wormhole, <em>and</em> working with the Foundation? I sure hope that man gets good pay.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="toc7"><span>Week of March 8th</span></h3>
<p>Not too many articles this week, but a good haul nonetheless. Hopefully you'll be entertained, for WAN.</p>
<h4 id="toc8"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2246">SCP-2246</a> (&quot;You Set the Scene&quot;) - A writer sits in their nothingness, toiling away at story after story. An activity once done for a friend is now subject to strangers, and that's more terrifying than any other possibility. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005044&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="Decibelles" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005044)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;">Decibelles</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc9"><span>Tales</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/basic-observations">Basic Observations</a> - As many continue to die as a result of forces unknown, a council meets and deliberates on how to best take action. But even amongst the Church, there's no sure answer. Trouble may be brewing&#8230; Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1621343&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="SunnyClockwork" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1621343)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;">SunnyClockwork</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc10"><span>Author Pages</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/univine-s-author-page">Univine's Author Page</a> - <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/univine" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(276792); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=276792&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="Univine" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=276792)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/univine" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(276792); return false;">Univine</a></span>'s author page! It only occurred to me now that this guy really likes writing good history skips. And on a side-note, collegiate quizbowl sounds fun as heck.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc11"><span>Misc.</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/sarkicism-hub">Sarkicism Hub</a> - Ultimately, it is feared that the Foundation and GOC know only a fraction of what Sarkicism entails and what its followers intend. Based on available information, the speculated goals of Sarkic cults nevertheless represent an SK-class dominance shift, including the possibility of an XK-class end-of-the-word scenario. Compiled, at last, by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/metaphysician" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1698079); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1698079&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="Metaphysician" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1698079)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/metaphysician" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1698079); return false;">Metaphysician</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="toc12"><span>Week of March 15th</span></h3>
<p>I heard that The Broken God and the Reverse Cyborg were making out. It was pretty sickly sweet, and gross.</p>
<h4 id="toc13"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2878">SCP-2878</a> (&quot;Reverse Cyborg&quot;) - This terrifying beast will do more than hunt and kill. Those human parts on it? Well, let's say you don't wanna be caught by this. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/terrorforge" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(658038); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=658038&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="Terrorforge" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=658038)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/terrorforge" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(658038); return false;">Terrorforge</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/twistedgears-kaktus-proposal">SCP-001</a> (&quot;The Broken God&quot;) - Lo, and I saw there upon the hills the wrath of the MEKHANE, the machine that will devour the world. The earth beneath our feet was torn asunder by its fists, the skies, the skies were blackened by its breath, and our ears were filled with the echo of its hate. He who was Broken has been undone, and the universe shall be reforged in his image. Brought to life by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1735681&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="TwistedGears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1735681)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;">TwistedGears</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-1595-j">SCP-1595-J</a> (&quot;Sweethearts&quot;) - God, what disgustingly sweet romantic partners. This is gross. Who even says things like &quot;It's like the mosquito of passion that buzzes in my ear!&quot;! Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/timmytim" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2617518); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2617518&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608435027" alt="TimmyTim" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2617518)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/timmytim" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2617518); return false;">TimmyTim</a></span>.</li>
